comment:
* The AppSearch Schema for a particular type of document. * *

For example, an e-mail message or a music recording could be a schema type. * *

The schema consists of type information, properties, and config (like tokenization type). * * @see AppSearchSession#setSchema

methods.name: private void appendAppSearchSchemaString(@NonNull IndentingStringBuilder builder)
methods.comment:
* Appends a debugging string for the {@link AppSearchSchema} instance to the given string
     * builder.
     *
     * @param builder the builder to append to.

methods.name: public String getSchemaType()
methods.comment: Returns the name of this schema type, such as Email.

methods.name: public String getDescription()
methods.comment:
* Returns a natural language description of this schema type. * *

Ex. The description for an Email type could be "A type of electronic message". * *

This information is purely to help apps consuming this type to understand its semantic * meaning. This field has no effect in AppSearch - it is just stored with the AppSearchSchema. * If {@link Builder#setDescription} is uncalled, then this method will return an empty string.

methods.name: public List<PropertyConfig> getProperties()
methods.comment:
* Returns the list of {@link PropertyConfig}s that are part of this schema. * *

This method creates a new list when called.

methods.name: public List<String> getParentTypes()
methods.comment: Returns the list of parent types of this schema for polymorphism.

methods.name: public void writeToParcel(@NonNull Parcel dest, int flags)
